LanguageData.WoodLog_Birch.label: birch logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Birch.description: Raw wood from a birch tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Birch is a perishable hardwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Palm.label: black palm logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Palm.description: Raw wood from a black palm tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Black palm is a durable wood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Cecropia.label: cecropia logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Cecropia.description: Raw wood from a cecropia tree. When processed it becomes useful in weapons, tools, handicrafts, small structures, and even simple prosthetics. Cecropia is a nondurable to perishable hardwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Cocoa.label: cocoawood logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Cocoa.description: Raw wood from a cocoa tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and simple prosthetics. Cocoawood is a nondurable hardwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Cypress.label: cypress logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Cypress.description: Raw wood from a cypress tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Cypress is a durable softwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Drago.label: drago logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Drago.description: Raw wood from a drago tree. When processed it becomes useful for making tools, handicrafts, and other makeshift structures. Drago is a low durability hardwood valued more for its resin.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Maple.label: maple logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Maple.description: Raw wood from a maple tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Maple is a nondurable to perishable hardwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Oak.label: oak logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Oak.description: Raw wood from an oak tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Oak is a very durable hardwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Pine.label: pine logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Pine.description: Raw wood from a pine tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Pine is a moderate to low durability softwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Poplar.label: poplar logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Poplar.description: Raw wood from a poplar tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Poplar is a nondurable hardwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Succulent.label: succulent ribs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Succulent.description: Ribs from a woody succulent like Saguaro cacti or semi-succulent like ocotillo. Succulent ribs are soft and excellent for making tools, handicrafts, fences, and other small structures.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Teak.label: teak logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Teak.description: Raw wood from a teak tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Teak is the most durable hardwood.
LanguageData.WoodLog_Willow.label: willow logs
LanguageData.WoodLog_Willow.description: Raw wood from a willow tree. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Willow is a nondurable hardwood.
LanguageData.Bamboo.label: bamboo
LanguageData.Bamboo.description: Raw bamboo. When processed it becomes useful for building structures, weapons, and even simple prosthetics. Bamboo is a perishable, fast growing grass.
